+# Colibri iMX6ULL Pantavisor Image: Installation Guide
+
+This guide explains how to install and boot the **Pantavisor Linux** image on a **Colibri iMX6ULL** module using the **Toradex Easy Installer (TEZI)**.
+
+---
+
+## Ô∏è Prerequisites
+
+* **Colibri iMX6ULL module** with USB OTG support.
+* Host PC with a USB port.
+* **Toradex Easy Installer** downloaded and extracted.
+* **FAT32-formatted USB drive** for image transfer (often called a 'USB stick' or 'Pendrive').
+
+---
+
+## 1. Download the Toradex Easy Installer
+
+1.  Download the appropriate TEZI package for your system:
+    <https://tezi.toradex.com/artifactory/tezi-oe-prod-frankfurt/scarthgap-7.x.y/release/5/colibri-imx6ull/tezi/tezi-run/oedeploy/Colibri-iMX6ULL_ToradexEasyInstaller_7.2.0+build.5.zip>
+2.  Extract the downloaded **ZIP archive** to a folder on your PC.
+
+---
+
+## 2. Load TEZI onto the Board (Recovery Mode)
+
+Follow the official Toradex instructions to load the Easy Installer onto your module via recovery mode:
+<https://developer.toradex.com/easy-installer/toradex-easy-installer/loading-toradex-easy-installer>
+
+### Quick Steps:
+
+1.  Set the board's boot selection to **USB OTG** (usually via a recovery jumper on the SOM).
+2.  Connect the **USB OTG port** on the base board (Aster, Iris, or Evaluation Board) to your PC's USB port.
+3.  Navigate to the extracted `Colibri-iMX6ULL_ToradexEasyInstaller` folder and run the recovery script:
+    ```bash
+    ./recovery-linux.sh
+    ```
+4.  For detailed information on the process, refer to the Toradex documentation.
+
+---
+
+## 3. Flash the Pantavisor Image
+
+1.  Extract the Pantavisor image archive (e.g., `pv-tar.xz`) to the root of your USB drive.
+2.  Plug the USB drive into the base board.
+3.  **TEZI** will automatically start the flashing process to the SOM's internal flash memory. Monitor the progress using the TEZI GUI on the display.
+4.  For more information on installing OS images with TEZI, see:
+    <https://developer.toradex.com/easy-installer/toradex-easy-installer/flashing-new-image-using-tezi/#install-os-images>
+
+---
+
+## 4. Boot the Image
+
+1.  Once the image flashing is complete, simply **reboot the board**.
+2.  Access the console via a **serial connection** to follow the boot sequence and monitor the system startup.
+
+---
+
+## 5. Next Steps
